    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from what it says to the author's intent in his original context, the chapter's place in the larger canonical argument, and the theological weight the narrative carries. The movements below trace the chapter's argument from David's impossible position through the providential escape and its implications for understanding divine faithfulness to flawed covenant servants.",
